	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have followed the diskussion so far with great interest. Altough my attempts to find a Xakra-Shield have been futile.<br><br>But I have gathered a couple of interesting facts for you to think about:<br><br>1. There are two Types of Xakra Armor: Xakra Kel (which as we know drops from Shades) and Xakra Dat (which was confirmed to drop from Shak Dratha)<br><br>2. The Shak Dratha &quot;Shadeweaver&quot; has been spottet oftenly in the Tunnels near the Loda Kai camp. When killed, he until today did not drop more then coin. There is no reportet attempt to hail/trade/interact with him yet, since noone had (enough?) faction with the Shak Dratha.<br><br>3. When you kill one race of &quot;little Aliens&quot; the other race spawns in its place, meaning: If you kill the Gor Taku blacksmith, who is known to trade with you (if you have faction with them) the shak dratha blacksmith spawns. Yet it seems unclear if he will trade with you too, since there was always hide/sneak or invis or bad faction involved in the reportet tries.<br><br>4. It is commonly believed that the whisperling quest starts with the Claw Needle action. Yet neither that Claw Needle nor any of the involved Items seemed to be of any use with the whisperling quest until now, which makes me, as a passionate RPG-Gamemaster very suspicious.<br><br>5. It is unconfirmed, that shades drop anything else but xakra kel armor pieces. They have not yet been seen to drop Weapons or Shields.<br><br>6.1 If you assume that there is a logic and a &quot;grand strategy&quot; behind the Vah Shir quests, you can assume too that the Gor Taku are the &quot;bad guys&quot; and the shak dratha are the &quot;good guys&quot;. To get the &quot;Blessed Championship Cloak of the Vah Shir&quot;, you gotta kill zillions of Loda Kai, therefore ruining the faction with the Gor Taku.<br><br>6.2 Many quests in Shar Vahl and Thicket are about &quot;Xakra&quot;, &quot;Whisperlings&quot; and lastly &quot;Ruining Faction with the Gor Taku&quot;. Unless there is a diabolic twist in the plot, it looks like the quest-designers wanted to lead you straight into a &quot;bad gor-taku faction&quot; and so opening the way to get &quot;good shak dratha faction&quot;, since most questers wont attack somebody, they already have a good faction with. Why did they let us start with a good gor taku faction when the quests will ruin it anyway? Maybe so we can finaly befriend the shak dratha?<br><br>7. Just because some ppl are dubious to the shak dratha, doesn't necessarily mean they will help you. Maybe you'll have to be even higher in their regard.<br><br>8. All shields made of carapaces or the like have been named after the mobs/items they are made of. It does not seem logical to me, that a swirling shadow/condensed shadow/etc. shield would finaly be called a Xakra Shield.<br><br>9. Regarding Scorpialis, I don't think that we'll need that dagger at that moment of the quest. Ragnar and the others mentioned it, but said nothing about bringing it or even needing it. They just say it would be out there.<br><br>Finally it will come down to that:<br><br>Is the shield dropped, or built/bought?<br>If it drops, it will drop from the shak dratha. If it's bought or hand-made, the knowledge or quest or merchant for it will also come from the shak dratha.<br><br>Questions:<br><br>1. Have Shak Dratha or Gor Taku been seen in other zones?<br><br>2. Have any mobs been seen in other zones, which have anything to do with xakra or weaving?<br><br>3. Has anyone seen Xakra Kel or even Xakra Dat Armor Weapons?<br><br>4. Can anyone definetly confirm the existens of silk other then shadeling silk, namely the rumored shadow silk or has their been just a confusion in the names?<br><br>5. I always read about about a tatterd buckler?!? Enlighten me! How can it be made?<br><br>6. Has there been a positive contact with a Shadeweaver or the shak Dratha Smith yet and what faction did the contacter have?<br><br>7. It was said, that Scorpialis was a dead end quest with a broken end. Did I miss something? I did the quest, got the dagger, but I didn't realise there was more to come. It seemed finished to me, but if somebody knows/suggests more, it could well be the hint we need!<br><br>Darklilly, Shaman, Vallon Zek<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
