	   <tr><td colspan=2>I've taken my monk to the room with the smiths.&nbsp;&nbsp;Using sneak, I can buy from the Gor smith, and the shield is called a palocht.  When you kill him, his corpse disappears, just like any other merchant.  The Shak smith doesn't sell anything, and his corpse remains when killed.  I had to use FD/sneak to deal with him.  No response to hails either.  There's also a brewer in that room, and the Gor/Shak versions work the same way.  I gave a shield I bought from the Gor to the Shak smith, and all that happened is he equipped it.<br><br>One other thing.  When you kill one of the static spawns in the caverns, a member of the other race usually spawns.  So if you kill the Gor smith, the Shak smith will spawn in it's place.  That's why you usually find the cavern filled with Gor.  Since they usually leave people alone, people kill all the Shak in the area, and move on.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
